---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'SafetyWing in Vietnam', level: 2 },
  { id: 'coverage', text: 'What SafetyWing Covers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'limitations', text: 'Limitations', level: 2 },
  { id: 'plans-and-pricing', text: 'Plans and Pricing', level: 2 },
  { id: 'who-its-for', text: 'Who Should Choose SafetyWing', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Health Insurance in Vietnam', href: '/countries/vietnam/insurance' },
  { title: 'SafetyWing Review', href: '/providers/safetywing' },
  { title: 'SafetyWing vs Cigna', href: '/compare/safetywing-vs-cigna-global' },
];

const planColumns = [
  { key: 'plan', header: 'Plan' },
  { key: 'coverage', header: 'Coverage' },
  { key: 'price', header: 'Price' },
];

const planRows = [
  { plan: 'Nomad Insurance', coverage: 'Travel medical', price: '$45-70/mo' },
  { plan: 'Remote Health', coverage: 'Health insurance', price: '$160-220/mo' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="SafetyWing in Vietnam"
  description="Guide to using SafetyWing in Vietnam. Popular travel medical insurance for digital nomads in Ho Chi Minh City, Hanoi, and Da Nang."
  headline="SafetyWing in Vietnam"
  subheadline="Popular travel medical insurance for digital nomads in Vietnam. What it covers and what it doesn't."
  heroBackgroundImage="/images/countries/vietnam-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Get a SafetyWing Quote"
  ctaButtonHref="/providers/safetywing"
>
  <h2 id="overview">SafetyWing in Vietnam</h2>
  <p>
    SafetyWing is popular among digital nomads in Vietnam's growing remote work scene—particularly in Ho Chi Minh City, Hanoi, and Da Nang. At $45/month, it provides affordable travel medical coverage for healthy individuals.
  </p>
  <p>
    Vietnam's very affordable healthcare makes SafetyWing a reasonable choice for emergency coverage, since you can easily pay for routine care out of pocket.
  </p>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-600">$45/mo</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Starting price</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-600">$250K</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Maximum coverage</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-600">$100K</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Evacuation coverage</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <CTABox
    title="Quick Coverage for Vietnam"
    description="SafetyWing is easy to purchase and starts immediately."
    buttonText="Get SafetyWing"
    buttonHref="/providers/safetywing"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="coverage">What SafetyWing Covers</h2>
  <p>
    SafetyWing Nomad Insurance includes:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Emergency medical:</strong> Up to $250,000</li>
    <li><strong>Hospital stays:</strong> Covered after deductible</li>
    <li><strong>Emergency dental:</strong> Pain relief and emergency care</li>
    <li><strong>Medical evacuation:</strong> $100,000 (to Bangkok/Singapore)</li>
    <li><strong>Trip interruption:</strong> Some coverage included</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>How It Works in Vietnam</h3>
  <p>
    SafetyWing operates on a reimbursement basis. Pay for care at Vietnamese hospitals (FV Hospital, Vinmec) and submit claims for reimbursement. Given Vietnam's low costs, this is manageable for most expats.
  </p>

  <h2 id="limitations">Limitations</h2>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-3">What SafetyWing Doesn't Cover</h3>
    <ul class="space-y-2 text-amber-800">
      <li><strong>Pre-existing conditions:</strong> Completely excluded</li>
      <li><strong>Routine care:</strong> Checkups, preventive care not covered</li>
      <li><strong>Mental health:</strong> Not covered</li>
      <li><strong>Maternity:</strong> Not covered (except emergency complications)</li>
      <li><strong>Chronic conditions:</strong> Ongoing treatment not covered</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h3>Vietnam Context</h3>
  <p>
    The good news: Vietnam's routine care is so cheap ($15-30 for a GP visit) that paying out of pocket is easy. SafetyWing's emergency coverage provides a safety net for serious events while you handle routine care yourself.
  </p>

  <h2 id="plans-and-pricing">Plans and Pricing</h2>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={planColumns} rows={planRows} />
  </div>

  <h3>Nomad Insurance vs Remote Health</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Nomad Insurance ($45/mo):</strong> Travel medical. Best for healthy nomads in Vietnam.</li>
    <li><strong>Remote Health ($160+/mo):</strong> Actual health insurance. Better for longer stays or those wanting comprehensive coverage.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="who-its-for">Who Should Choose SafetyWing in Vietnam</h2>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-green-900 mb-3">Good Fit</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-green-800">
        <li>Healthy digital nomads</li>
        <li>Short to medium stays</li>
        <li>Budget-conscious travelers</li>
        <li>Those with no pre-existing conditions</li>
        <li>Expats comfortable with limitations</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Consider Alternatives</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
        <li>Long-term expats (1+ years)</li>
        <li>Anyone with pre-existing conditions</li>
        <li>Those needing mental health coverage</li>
        <li>Families with children</li>
        <li>Retirees</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h3>The Bottom Line</h3>
  <p>
    SafetyWing works well for Vietnam's digital nomad scene. The combination of affordable travel medical insurance plus cheap out-of-pocket routine care is practical for healthy individuals. For longer stays or health concerns, consider international health insurance.
  </p>

  <CTABox
    title="Need More Than SafetyWing?"
    description="Compare comprehensive international health insurance for Vietnam."
    buttonText="See All Options"
    buttonHref="/countries/vietnam/insurance"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> SafetyWing Nomad Insurance is travel medical insurance with limitations. Review policy details carefully before purchasing.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
